BEAVER BOARD COMPANIES, Plaintiff, v. James IMBRIE, et al., Defendants, and Madelaine H. West, Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 4, 1925.) No. 354. Ferris, Shepard, Joyce & McCoy, of New York City (John E. Joyce, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Rabenold & Scribner, of New York City (Ralph M. Ketch-am. of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed in open court.
